data.name: label2.Text
data.value: Begin by affixing a resistance band to a fixed object at lower chest level height. Next, grab hold of the provided handles or the bands themselves if no handles are provided with an overhand grip. Stand with your feet in a staggered stance with your back upright. Arms should straight out in front of your body with your hands at lower chest level. Begin exercise by pulling your hands to your ears, while keeping your palms facing down throughout the movement. Briefly hold this position to get a good contraction, then slowly lower your hands back down to the starting position. This completes one rep.
